      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic continuum mechanics with frictional contact; justified by operating regime below yield for stiffness QoI. Required level 3 because model form assumptions directly govern prediction accuracy for the primary QoI. Validation against N=11 experimental specimens confirms model form adequacy.",
      "rationale": "The model employs linear elastic material laws with isotropic properties for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V). Frictional contact (mu=0.3) is applied at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces. Model form is appropriate for the sub-yield loading regime targeted by ASTM F1717 stiffness measurement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certified mill certificates for each lot; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of five representative screws. Required level 3 because input uncertainty directly propagates to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus and Poisson's ratio for Ti-6Al-4V taken from certified material test reports (mean E=114 GPa, nu=0.34). Screw geometry digitized via coordinate measuring machine. Input uncertainty quantified using Monte Carlo sampling (500 runs); coefficient of variation on stiffness QoI is 2.1%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled and tested; sample size justified by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect 10% QoI difference. Required level 3 consistent with medium model risk and need for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-representative hardware across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes). Sample variability characterised; coefficient of variation on experimental stiffness is 4.3%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load condition (ASTM F1717 compression-bending at 5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated, limiting coverage of the loading envelope. Gradation 2 achieved against a required Gradation 3; this shortfall is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation dataset."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions mapped directly to test fixture geometry. Applied displacement rate confirmed quasi-static (inertial effects negligible). Input parameter equivalency verified by independent reviewer."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric (Oberkampf & Roy); acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 (95% confidence interval). Required level 3 because quantitative probabilistic comparison is necessary to substantiate medium-risk model claims. All three QoIs must satisfy threshold.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (0.82), yield force (1.14), and force at 40 mm (1.31). All values fall below the 1.96 threshold, confirming model predictions are within experimental uncertainty bounds. Gradation 3 achieved for all three QoIs."
    },
    {
